structured.title: WWE Builds To Elimination Chamber And Honors AJ Styles
structured.overview: This content is a stitched-together set of WWE TV segments and commentary focused on building hype for the upcoming Elimination Chamber event and celebrating AJ Styles. It includes a promo from Trick Williams hyping his first Elimination Chamber match in Atlanta, comedic interaction and tension around AJ Styles and others backstage, and Paul Heyman (the "Oracle") issuing an open challenge on behalf of Brock Lesnar for WrestleMania while questioning whether anyone is brave enough to accept. Becky Lynch and another female star trade barbs over accolades, legacy, and an upcoming title match in Chicago, with Becky set to defend against a hometown opponent AJ Lee in a one-on-one match, her first singles title shot in over a decade. Commentary then recaps qualifiers and injuries for both the men's and women's Elimination Chamber matches, including Bronson Reed‚Äôs distal biceps tear ruling him out indefinitely. The women‚Äôs Chamber lineup is highlighted, with the winner earning a WrestleMania match against Jade Cargill. Jade is interviewed about Liv Morgan declaring for WrestleMania and confidently dismisses her competition. Additional segments promote the WWE 2K26 video game centered on CM Punk‚Äôs career and show in-ring and backstage tributes to AJ Styles, praising his 25-year career, influence on the business, and his role as a family man, culminating in a heartfelt thank‚Äëyou package for Styles.

## Elimination Chamber build  
- Jey Uso qualifies as final men's chamber entrant  
- Trick Williams cuts confident promo for chamber match  
- Men's chamber winner to face Drew McIntyre at WrestleMania  

## Brock Lesnar WrestleMania open challenge  
- Paul Heyman issues open challenge for Lesnar at WrestleMania  
- Emphasizes Lesnar ending Undertaker‚Äôs WrestleMania streak  
- Claims no one has courage to accept Lesnar‚Äôs challenge  

## Becky Lynch vs AJ Lee build  
- Becky insults AJ‚Äôs career and CM Punk  
- AJ returns for first singles match in decade  
- Match for Intercontinental title in AJ‚Äôs hometown Chicago  

## AJ Styles tribute and farewell  
- Multiple wrestlers praise AJ‚Äôs 25 year career  
- Called ‚Äúone of a kind‚Äù and ‚Äúphenomenal‚Äù  
- Emotional in ring celebration and goodbyes in Chicago  

## Women‚Äôs division updates  
- Raquel Rodriguez wins triple threat, qualifies for chamber  
- Bronson Reed suffers distal biceps tear, out indefinitely  
- Women‚Äôs chamber: Rhea, Tiffany, Alexa, Asuka, Kiana, Raquel  

## Jade Cargill WrestleMania situation  
- Liv Morgan declares for WrestleMania vs Stephanie  
- Jade lists accolades: 2x tag champ, 2025 Queen of the Ring  
- Says she doesn‚Äôt fear any potential challengers  

## Next steps  
- Men‚Äôs and women‚Äôs chamber winners head to WrestleMania  
- AJ Lee vs Becky Lynch decides Intercontinental champion  
- Await someone accepting Brock Lesnar‚Äôs open WrestleMania challenge
